headline.main: CALLS HULL AGAIN ON NEUTRALITY LAW; President in Second Talk on Change Maps Details to Be Laid Before Congress TO SEE CHIEFS NEXT WEEK Senator Schwartz Appeals on Radio for Full Support of Our Foreign Policy

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Oct. 1 -- President Roosevelt continued discussions with Secretary Hull today, preparatory to what is expected to be an open appeal for substantial modification, or practical repeal of the Neutrality Act of 1939.
